title: Milwaukee Brewers shut out Rangers, Brinson has 3 hits
text:
Brewers shut out Rangers, Brinson has 3 hits Pitcher Josh Hader helped the Milwaukee Brewers to a 5-0 shutout win over the Texas Rangers. Allan Henry-USA TODAY Sports Feb 27, 2017 at 8:39p ET 0Shares 
Lewis Brinson had three hits against his former team, driving in the go-ahead run to help the Milwaukee Brewers to a 5-0 win over the Texas Rangers. 
One of Milwaukeeâ€™s top prospects, Brinson was acquired by the Brewers in the trade that sent veteran catcher Jonathan Lucroy to the Rangers. 
Right-handed pitcher Junior Guerra made his first start of the spring, pitching one scoreless inning. 
Scooter Gennett added two hits with a walk. 0
